  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: \r\nWhen you are switching between chats instead of showing last message app scrolling through history and then jumps to last message (looks like flickering).\r\nDepends on laptop characteristics, glitches are shown ~50 ms (16 GB onboard memory)  to ~100-150 ms (4 GB onboard memory).\r\nCan be related to https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/5271\r\nAlso app jumps to last message if you scroll to the top of existing history  (in my case week ago).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1) no glitches when switching between chats  \r\n2) no redirecting to last message when scrolling to the top of chat history\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1) (slowed to see glitches)\r\n![glitch](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/44397598-96713f80-a549-11e8-8283-7cfd1e61ce1e.gif)\r\n2) chat history jumps to last message\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n*Scenario 1:*\r\n- Open Status Desktop\r\n- Open multiple chats and start switching between them\r\n\r\n*Scenario 2:*\r\n- Open Status Desktop\r\n- navigate to chat with longest history (i.e. > 1 week)\r\n- scroll to the top of chat history\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly 21/08/2018\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx\r\n* Video for scenario 2: http://take.ms/8Wx1N",
